    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Parts of a bridle that prevent a horse from opening its mouth wide enough to lay its tongue over the bit. It also keeps the bit stable.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
